column2: Partly cloudy but hazy and breezy.
Slight haze- air temp 60- slight ripple- visible particles in water
Clear day- air temp 68- slight ripple on water- N wind
Partly cloudy- slight breeze and ripple- water temp 72- floating particles (algae bloom)
Water temp 70- clear- sunny- slight ripple.
Water temp 74- partly cloudy- small ripples.
Water temp 75- scattered clouds- slight ripple on water- floating particles- air temp 76.
Water temp is 72 degrees- air temp is 60 degrees- ripples on the water- rain yesterday.
Ripples on the water- scattered clouds- wind and rain yesterday.  Water is cloudy- water temp is 67 degrees- air temp is 51 degrees.
North wind and small waves- due to wind and sun position I could not do test so view of disk was in shade and protected from waves.  Did test in shade and in waves.
Clear and sunny- slight ripples- NW wind- water temp is 60 degrees- air temp is 55 degrees.
It has been windy- white caps on the lake today- small waves at the test site.  Particles visible suspended in the water.  Clear and sunny- water is 52 degrees- air is 42 degrees.
Small ripples and clear and sunny- water temp is 52 degrees- air temp is 54 degrees.
Water temp is 48 degrees- air temp is 32 degrees- ripples on the water- mostly cloudy.  Water is not too clear- probably due to previous windy days.
Flies and dead smelt. Lake calm on this beautiful sunny 70 degree day.  May flies horribly abundant.  Many dead smelt in water.  Smelt catch was low this spring.  Loon surfaced at 100' from site #2.
Spring black- non-biting flies were thick- and the water temperature is 52 degrees F.
Calm lake.  Overcast skies.  Yellow powder on water is washing up on shore.  Big (12") suckers close to north shore in mass.
Partly cloudy-soft south breeze-heavy rain 5/29-beautiful day.
Rain most of 6/5-partly cloudy today-lake calm like mirror-beautiful day!
Water clear blue to about 10' then gradually greenish.  We have had heavy rain.  Green "scum" has washed in from swamps.  80 degree windy day-rough water-partly cloudy.  Water rough.
Water 66 degrees F- calm water- nearly smooth.
Water clear green after 10'.  Much "scum" (from swamp ) + vegetation. washed on the shore.  Calm lake today-partly cloudy.
Water temp. 69 degrees F- ripples on water.
Water clear green after 10'.  Swimmer's itch has been a problem.  Four eagles sighted over north shore trees.
Water 69 degrees F- particles in water and on surface- water nearly calm.
Much boat traffic after one week of clouds + rain.  Partly cloudy-beautiful now.
Water temp. 68 degrees F- particles in water- ripples on surface.
Water temp. 68 degrees F- ripples on water.
July was stormy-lake rough when we were home.  Much vegetation floating in lake + washing on shore.
Heavy rain continues to wash debris in lake.  Gravel from replaced culvert under e. fence lake rd. washed into bay.  Sandy colored water.
Calm water-partly cloudy-water much cleaner than earlier.  Four boats on lake-traffic way down.
Partly cloudy-calm water-sea weed vegetation + foam continues to float to shore.
Foam on shore-much sea weed floating-no wind-calm lake-beautiful sunny day.  Two loons sighted near #2 site.
Water temp. 62 degrees F- good test conditions.
Water clear green after 5'.  Heavy rain last week.  Much debris in water + washed on shore-3 loons sighted on way to #2.  Beautiful partly sunny day.
Partly sunny-70 degrees-south breeze.  Another week of rain.  Have never seen lake this high. jet skis are gone.  Less debris also.  Lake level: very high
Flow from swamp very heavy.  52 degrees-overcast-one other boat on lake-loon sighted near #2.
Water 56 degrees- air 42 degrees- choppy water.
Blue sky- the temperature is 55 degrees- and there is a light south breeze.  Boat goes in for winter 10/13/1994.
Water temperature is 56 degrees- the air temperature is 42 degrees- and there are slight ripples on the water.
Water 46 degrees- ripples on water- recent rains and winds.  Particles floating in water.  Last reading for '94.
Ripples on water- water 51 degrees F.
Water 54 degrees- partly cloudy- black spring flies at shore.
Spring flies at shore- water 54 degrees.
Slight haze- water smooth- water 62 degrees.
Water 79 degrees F!!  shad ( ) flies and pine pollen on water.
Water 56 degrees- floating particles in water.
Floating particles in water- temp. 66 degrees F.
Water temp. 66 degrees F. ripples on water May have reduced depth.
Water temp. @ 3': 70 degrees F- floating particles in water.
Partly cloudy- air temp is 65 degrees.
Mostly cloudy- air temp is 48 degrees.
Floating particles in the water.  Some clouds and a somewhat hazy sky.  Slight ripples on the water.  3.5 inches of rain in the last two weeks.
Sunny- 10-15 mph wind.  Took secchi reading away from the regular site where there was less wind and calmer water.  Rain gauge reading from 8/14 to 8/27 =3.1 inches.
Secchi disk reading took on 10/10.  On 10/22 it was too cloudy and water was too rough to take a Secchi reading.
Ice went out on 4/22/2001.  Pollen on the water.
Pollen floating on surface and suspended particles.
choppy water- not the best conditions
Ripples on water may have reduced secchi depth.
Measurements obtained 2 days after wind storm.
Clear- light wind. Measurement taken post rain and wind storm x 2 days.
Lake calm. Visible increase in phytoplankton compared to measurements of July 10.
Wind dead calm. Noticeable plankton suspended in water.
Over cast- calm water- and barely any boat traffic on the water.
Sunny- calm water- warm- and moderate boat traffic.
